Key Characteristics

  • Coastal tropical climate advantage
  • Excellent healthcare infrastructure. Modical tourism destination
  • Kochi demonstrates what Indian metros can achieve with coastal climate + excellent healthcare + high development

    *Synthetic Data Considerations

  • Population: ~3.6M (metro 2025); literacy 96.29%; sex ratio 1030/1000; child population (0-6) 9.39%
  • Respiratory Disease: Chronic respiratory symptoms in 9.2% population; chronic cough 8.7%, chronic bronchitis 6.19%, asthma 2.82%; rising respiratory infections noted after travel periods
  • Healthcare: One of India's best healthcare facilities; major medical tourism hub; Kochi Medical City project; General Hospital Ernakulam as key government facility; ₹10,431 crore state health budget allocation
  • Seasonal Patterns: Tropical monsoon climate; pleasant Sep-Feb; respiratory infections surge during travel seasons and weather transitions
  • Socioeconomic: Per capita income ₹372,783 (Kerala, 6th in India); Ernakulam district ranks first in Kerala's socio-economic development; major commercial hub
